# Frontend production configuration.
#
# In production there is no Vite dev proxy, so the app must call the API at
# its real origin. `VITE_API_BASE` is inlined into the build (it is a
# VITE_-prefixed var), so set it in your host's build environment (e.g. the
# Vercel project's Environment Variables) rather than committing a value.
#
# Copy this file to `.env.production` for a local production build, or set
# the variable in the Vercel dashboard for deploys.

# The backend's public HTTPS origin (no trailing slash). Requests to
# /simulation/* and /health are sent here. The backend must allow this app's
# origin via CORS (JSTC_CORS_ORIGINS on the API).
VITE_API_BASE=https://your-backend-host.example.com
